Gauteng remains the best place to be employed in a number of professions according to staff recruitment agency Career Junction s latest salary review.The review contains up-to-date salary information as well as regional differences on actual salary offerings for skilled and senior level candidates in the 10 most popular job sectors including finance ICT and engineering.These salary offerings which represent monthly cost to company remuneration were on the Career Junction website between April and October this year.In the engineering field senior civil engineers were being offered between R48 142 to R62 637 senior mechanical engineers between R46 816 to R57 287 and senior electronic engineers were offered between R39 306 and R 52 745.The survey found that salary offerings in the engineering field seemed to be considerably lower in the Western Cape compared to salary offerings in KwaZulu-Natal and Gauteng. This could possibly be due to a lower demand for skills in the Western Cape. In IT senior positions in project management ranged from R 40 067 to R 51 692 while senior positions in software development offered between R43 091 to R 52 761. The survey said when comparing earnings in the IT sector there seemed to be only a small difference between Gauteng and the Western Cape. However salary offerings in KwaZulu-Natal were notably lower compared to Gauteng and the Western Cape.In the design media and arts sector there were slight differences in remuneration among the three regions Gauteng was in the lead followed by Western Cape and KwaZulu-Natal.The survey found that Gauteng which is home to the largest stock exchange in Africa remains the highest-earning province for professionals in the financial sector. It said that due to the high demand for labour earnings were notably higher compared to Western Cape and Kwa-Zulu-Natal. Professionals in the Western Cape were offered between 18% to 26% less than their Gauteng counterparts while those in KwaZulu-Natal were offered between 33% and 35% less.The same trend could be seen in administration office and support where salaries in Gauteng were significantly higher compared to salaries in Western Cape and KwaZulu-Natal. Gauteng was also at the higher end of the remuneration scale for marketing professions compared to the Western Cape and KwaZulu-Natal.In sales Gauteng rates well above other provinces with KwaZulu-Natal second and the Western Cape in third. TMG Digital 